If you do not need nnpack then you can just turn it off by passing -DUSE_NNPACK=OFF to cmake.

Can you update to the latest code, clear out the build directory and old Caffe2 and Pytorch installations, and try again? This time pass VERBOSE=1 to your make command like make VERBOSE=1 install -j8 |& tee out_make and then upload the out_make file?

body:
If you do not need nnpack then you can just turn it off by passing -DUSE_NNPACK=OFF to cmake. 

Can you update to the latest code, clear out the build directory and old Caffe2 and Pytorch installations, and try again? This time pass VERBOSE=1 to your make command like `make VERBOSE=1 install -j8 |& tee out_make` and then upload the out_make file?
